<br>
The last year I played, I stayed because of my friends and my guild, I enjoyed playing with them...it had nothing to do with getting newer drops.<br>
<br>
I mean, I went to ToV only twice, because I found HoT raids the most boring thing in the world.  I thought about it and realized, for the time invested to get lucky on drops and acquire fiull SS armor...it simply wasn't worth it.  I mean, already having full Mrylo, I was happy enough.  Ok, so now I could invest 100 hours of time or more, killing mobs in assembly line fashion in ToV - simple and boring - and at the end of it I have a suit of SS armor.  Yay.  Now what?  Am I able to do anything *that* much better now with SS armor instead of what I had?  Not really.<br>
<br>
Getting WS armor in Hate was a lot more fun...it was actually a challenging zone you could have fun in...not a simple assembly line like ToV..."pull the next mob, everyone wait til MA has aggro, everyone assist, yay, mob's dead, enter the roll if armor drops, go pull the next one".  Ugh.  No thanks.<br>
<br>
I decided I'd rather spend the time helping guildmates with epics, doing Chardok Royals raids, taking less experienced guildmates who hadn't been to Hate and Fear very often on raids etc...  It was a lot more rewarding and productive use of my time.<br>
<br>
Anyways, it was friends that kept me playing, and exploring new areas - not the new items that dropped in these new areas.  Those are always secondary, not the goal or reason to play. <p><font size=4><font face=hanzel, verdana, arial black><b>Kuurus</font></b><BR><font size=2><font face=hanzel, verdana, arial black>Assassin and Guild Leader</font><BR><font size=2><font face=andy, hanzel, arial black><b><A HREF=http://pub52.ezboard.com/bwarcry97210>Cry of War</A></font></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/upedriccuf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pedric Cuf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/31/01 1:11:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseranthallgripeswishes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4350.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The steady increase in power of players</span><hr size=1> I'm one of those people who doesn't rush to 50. I've been 39 for who knows how long, and I can assure you that better weapons are definitely something I need. Like Kuurus, I'm in this game for my friends. I screw around with them, hunt with them, explore with them, it's much more fun then a quick exp grind up to 50. I look for newbies to help, I work up my trade skills and have newbie contests, from what I've seen, the high levels have no appeal for me. Where you have to get in a large guild to do anything. Where the only contest is who can drop the bigger mob and get the better armor. No thank you. I'm happy where I am. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafeh